verses.text_plain: The burden of Nineveh. The book of the vision of Nahum the Elkoshite.
verses.verse_html: 1The burden of Nineveh. The book of the vision of Nahum the Elkoshite.

verses.text_plain: God is jealous, and the Lord revengeth; the Lord revengeth, and is furious; the Lord will take vengeance on his adversaries, and he reserveth wrath for his enemies.
verses.verse_html:
2God is jealous, and the Lord revengeth; the Lord revengeth, and is furious; the Lord will take vengeance on his adversaries, and he reserveth wrath for his enemies. ▼
▼ God…: or, The Lord is a jealous God, and a revenger, etc
 , ▼
▼ is furious: Heb. that hath fury

footnotes.body_text: ▼ God…: or, The Lord is a jealous God, and a revenger, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ God…: or, The Lord is a jealous God, and a revenger, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ is furious: Heb. that hath fury
footnotes.body_html: ▼ is furious: Heb. that hath fury

verses.text_plain: The Lord is slow to anger, and great in power, and will not at all acquit the wicked: the Lord hath his way in the whirlwind and in the storm, and the clouds are the dust of his feet.
verses.verse_html: 3The Lord is slow to anger, and great in power, and will not at all acquit the wicked: the Lord hath his way in the whirlwind and in the storm, and the clouds are the dust of his feet.

verses.text_plain: He rebuketh the sea, and maketh it dry, and drieth up all the rivers: Bashan languisheth, and Carmel, and the flower of Lebanon languisheth.
verses.verse_html: 4He rebuketh the sea, and maketh it dry, and drieth up all the rivers: Bashan languisheth, and Carmel, and the flower of Lebanon languisheth.

verses.text_plain: The mountains quake at him, and the hills melt, and the earth is burned at his presence, yea, the world, and all that dwell therein.
verses.verse_html: 5The mountains quake at him, and the hills melt, and the earth is burned at his presence, yea, the world, and all that dwell therein.

verses.text_plain: Who can stand before his indignation? and who can abide in the fierceness of his anger? his fury is poured out like fire, and the rocks are thrown down by him.
verses.verse_html:
6Who can stand before his indignation? and who can abide in the fierceness of his anger? his fury is poured out like fire, and the rocks are thrown down by him. ▼
▼ abide: Heb. stand up

footnotes.body_html: ▼ abide: Heb. stand up

verses.text_plain: The Lord is good, a strong hold in the day of trouble; and he knoweth them that trust in him.
verses.verse_html:
7The Lord is good, a strong hold in the day of trouble; and he knoweth them that trust in him. ▼
▼ strong hold: or, strength

footnotes.body_html: ▼ strong hold: or, strength

verses.text_plain: But with an overrunning flood he will make an utter end of the place thereof, and darkness shall pursue his enemies.
verses.verse_html: 8But with an overrunning flood he will make an utter end of the place thereof, and darkness shall pursue his enemies.

verses.text_plain: What do ye imagine against the Lord? he will make an utter end: affliction shall not rise up the second time.
verses.verse_html: 9What do ye imagine against the Lord? he will make an utter end: affliction shall not rise up the second time.

verses.text_plain: For while they be folden together as thorns, and while they are drunken as drunkards, they shall be devoured as stubble fully dry.
verses.verse_html: 10For while they be folden together as thorns, and while they are drunken as drunkards, they shall be devoured as stubble fully dry.

verses.text_plain: There is one come out of thee, that imagineth evil against the Lord, a wicked counsellor.
verses.verse_html:
11There is one come out of thee, that imagineth evil against the Lord, a wicked counsellor. ▼
▼ a wicked…: Heb. a counsellor of Belial

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a wicked…: Heb. a counsellor of Belial
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a wicked…: Heb. a counsellor of Belial

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord; Though they be quiet, and likewise many, yet thus shall they be cut down, when he shall pass through. Though I have afflicted thee, I will afflict thee no more.
verses.verse_html:
12Thus saith the Lord; Though they be quiet, and likewise many, yet thus shall they be cut down, when he shall pass through. Though I have afflicted thee, I will afflict thee no more. ▼
▼ Though…: or, If they would have been at peace, so should they have been many, and so should they have been shorn, and he should have passed away
 , ▼
▼ cut down: Heb. shorn

tokens.text: yet thus shall they be cut down

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Though…: or, If they would have been at peace, so should they have been many, and so should they have been shorn, and he should have passed away
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Though…: or, If they would have been at peace, so should they have been many, and so should they have been shorn, and he should have passed away
▼ cut down: Heb. shorn

verses.text_plain: For now will I break his yoke from off thee, and will burst thy bonds in sunder.
verses.verse_html: 13For now will I break his yoke from off thee, and will burst thy bonds in sunder.

tokens.text: from off thee, and will burst

verses.text_plain: And the Lord hath given a commandment concerning thee, that no more of thy name be sown: out of the house of thy gods will I cut off the graven image and the molten image: I will make thy grave; for thou art vile.
verses.verse_html: 14And the Lord hath given a commandment concerning thee, that no more of thy name be sown: out of the house of thy gods will I cut off the graven image and the molten image: I will make thy grave; for thou art vile.

verses.text_plain: Behold upon the mountains the feet of him that bringeth good tidings, that publisheth peace! O Judah, keep thy solemn feasts, perform thy vows: for the wicked shall no more pass through thee; he is utterly cut off.
verses.verse_html:
15Behold upon the mountains the feet of him that bringeth good tidings, that publisheth peace! O Judah, keep thy solemn feasts, perform thy vows: for the wicked shall no more pass through thee; he is utterly cut off. ▼
▼ keep…: Heb. feast
 , ▼
▼ the wicked: Heb. Belial

tokens.text: of him that bringeth good tidings
thee; he is utterly cut off
